{"word":"τρυγάω","slug":"τρυγάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>τρυγάω</el></b> [<el>τρύγη</el> ‘a harvest’] ‘gather in ripe produce’, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> <b>harvest (grapes)<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> of the fruit, the grapes <b><a href='B:490 6:44'>Lk 6:44</a>; <a href='B:730 14:18'>Rv 14:18</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> of the source of the fruit, the grapevine <b><a href='B:730 14:19'>Rv 14:19</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:τρύβλιον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:τρυγών\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}